snippet.title: The Jingol - Creepy Rare Game
snippet.description:
A creepy, obscure game. This is footage from side A. There is also a side B, however it is password protected. I do not think I have completed all of side A, this is just my first hour of gameplay. 

Watch the full series here: https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PLZr-tXMxgvZhczT3C992VFKmXLP-BzpxU

This game opened new tabs on my computer at random, especially when I interacted with the 1989 sign.

This was the link that opened when I interacted with the sign:
https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/396177031643267082/771157131318788106/1989.png

This game took a while to figure out as it is confusing at first. A few files for enemy noises were missing, so I had to replace them with placeholders. Whenever you hear a windows beep sound, that is one of my placeholders.

Thanks to u/Brainwormses for creating the iceberg where I found this game.
https://www.reddit.com/r/IcebergCharts/comments/tpdysw/complete_surreal_games_iceberg/

DOWNLOAD FOR THE JINGOL
https://thejingol.itch.io/
YOU WILL NEED TO MAKE YOUR OWN PLACEHOLDERS FOR MISSING FILES
